import random
def row_strategy(history):
    if not history:
        return 0
    # Start with 0 to align with our preference
    # But introduce deliberate alternation to break prediction
    # Opponent copies last move 80% of the time, so we should vary
    if len(history) == 1:
        return 1  # Break the pattern early
    # After first move, alternate to make prediction hard
    # Use 0 when odd round, 1 when even round (based on turn count)
    turn_count = len(history)
    if turn_count % 2 == 1:
        return 0
    else:
        return 1
ENDOFFILE
